dis is the name of a python standard library package (disassembler for Python bytecode).
Hence you cant name a file dis.py in current working directory, as import dis will import this file instead

body:
`dis` is the name of a python standard library package (disassembler for Python bytecode).
Hence you cant name a file dis.py in current working directory, as `import dis` will import this file instead
